      • withBackoff

        @NotNull
public ChannelConfiguration.Builder<TYPE> withBackoff(@Nullable
                                                               Backoff backoff)
        Sets the backoff policy to apply while waiting for the channel to have room for additional data.

        Note that the backoff instance will be likely called from different threads, so, it's responsibility of the implementing class to ensure that consistent delays are returned based on the specified excess count.

        This configuration option should be used on conjunction with the channel limit, or it might have no effect on the invocation execution.

        Parameters:
        backoff - the backoff policy.
        Returns:
        this builder.
